Step 5 of the installer (`05-fix-cellular.sh`) constructs a modified
copy of `/usr/sbin/ofonod` (ofono-sailfish 1.29+git12, GPL-2.0) on the
user's own device using documented byte-offset patches. The patches
themselves are derived from analysis of GPL-licensed upstream sources
(ofono, ofono-binder-plugin, libgbinder-radio); see `installer/README.md`
and inline comments in `05-fix-cellular.sh` for the corresponding source
references. To honor the upstream licensing chain, this repository is
released under GPL-2.0-or-later.

Upstream component sources:
  - ofono / ofono-sailfish:   https://github.com/sailfishos/ofono
  - ofono-binder-plugin:      https://github.com/mer-hybris/ofono-binder-plugin
  - libgbinder-radio:         https://github.com/mer-hybris/libgbinder-radio

External tools fetched by the installer at runtime keep their own
licenses (bkerler/edl: GPL-3.0; bkerler/oppo_decrypt: GPL-3.0;
Magisk magiskboot binary: GPL-3.0; Android platform-tools: Apache-2.0).
